extendedInfo.description: Lookup aircraft by the Tail Number to search FAA data for more information about that aircraft, such as model, engine, seats, owner, and more.Version 1.8 allows you to choose which items you would like to display in the results.  Use the Menu button and click on Prefs.  Uncheck items you no longer want to see and they will not be displayed on your search.Now decodes items such as Aircraft Type, Engine Type, Builder Certification Code, Registrant Type, Owner Region, and Status Code.Android 2.2 users now have the option to put application on SD Card.Note: FAA only has info on US based aircraft.  Database updated monthly from FAA data.  If it doesn't return the number, it's not a United States based aircraft.  Do not give bad reviews if it does not find all the planes on your European vacation.  This only covers domestic registered aircraft from the United States of America.If you have any questions, comments or suggestions please email them to lifebytessoftware@gmail.comIf you like this free application please take the time to come back to the market and rate this software.

reviews.title: Handy app!
reviews.comment: It\'s simple & shows loads of data on aircraft. I tried a few of these apps and although the other LOOK nicer, they do not work as well.  I\'d rather have 2-3 times more data on the aircraft than a nice UI.
reviews.author: A Google User
